text: Selah High School is a public high school located in Selah, Washington, United States, serving students in grades 9–12. It is part of the Selah School District and enrolls approximately 1000 students yearly. The school colors are blue and gold, and the mascot is the Vikings. Selah excels in its excellent academics, Career Tecnical Programs (FCCLA, FFA, TSA) as well as in its sports. The volleyball and baseball programs are among the best in their state at any classification. All other Selah sports also compete at a very high level. Selah offers an assortment of classes to prepare kids for their future and takes pride in helping kids achieve their goals. Selah is a tight knit community and a great place to raise a family. ==Notable alumni== * Garret Dillahunt, actor (Deadwood, The 4400, ER, Terminator: The Sarah Connor Chronicles, Raising Hope) * Craig Kupp, former NFL player ==References== == External links == *Selah HS Website Category:High schools in Yakima County, Washington Category:Public high schools in Washington (state)
title: Selah High School
